<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FFFC6A43F82D912C1863B39A" pageId="7" pageNumber="765" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFFFC6A43F82D912C1863B39A" blockId="7.[1996,2595,1752,2179]" lastBlockId="7.[1383,2593,2183,3282]" pageId="7" pageNumber="765">
The phylogenetic position of N. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFFC6A43F655912C1403BCA4" authorityName="Imaizumi &amp; Yoshiyuki" authorityYear="1968" box="[2473,2563,1909,1942]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Nyctalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="765" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="furvus">furvus</taxonomicName>
is uncertain, but the species has a similar karyotype to N. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFFC6A43F74E919D16FFBCD7" baseAuthorityName="Kuhl" baseAuthorityYear="1817" box="[2226,2303,1988,2021]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Nyctalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="765" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="leisleri">leisleri</taxonomicName>
, indicating that they may be closely related. However, based on morphology, N. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFFC6A43F7409E4A1716B306" authorityName="Imaizumi &amp; Yoshiyuki" authorityYear="1968" box="[2236,2326,2067,2100]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Nyctalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="765" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="furvus">furvus</taxonomicName>
is most similar to N. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFFC6A43F8029E63165CB369" authorityName="Schreber" authorityYear="1774" box="[2046,2140,2106,2139]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Nyctalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="765" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="noctula">noctula</taxonomicName>
and N. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFFC6A43F72F9E631731B369" baseAuthorityName="Gerbe" baseAuthorityYear="1880" box="[2259,2353,2106,2139]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Nyctalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="765" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="plancyi">plancyi</taxonomicName>
, and the species has variously been included in either of these. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
