<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FFFC6A43FA9B9D2F18B9B0D7" pageId="7" pageNumber="765" type="activity">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFFFC6A43FA9B9D2F18B9B0D7" blockId="7.[1383,2593,2183,3282]" pageId="7" pageNumber="765">
<emphasis id="F6E0EAECFFFC6A43FA9B9D2F1852B0A5" bold="true" box="[1383,1618,2934,2967]" pageId="7" pageNumber="765">Activity patterns.</emphasis>
Like their congeners, Japanese Noctules are probably nocturnal and hibernate through the winter. Roosts occurin tree hollows, and a hibernating colony was found in a building.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
